                                          Junction Object
                                        --------------------
 A junction object in Salesforce is a custom object used to create a many-to-many relationship between two other objects.

  Problem without junction object.
--------------------------------------
          1). Rahul wants to take Math, Physics, and Chemistry. need to create 3 records, data redundency happen.
          2). Math class needs to have Rahul, Priya, and Amit. again data redundency.
          3). You can't put all three courses into a single field on Rahul's profile.
          4). You can't put all three students into a single field on the Math course record.
          5). If you duplicate Rahul’s actual profile three times (Rahul-Math, Rahul-Physics, Rahul-Chemistry)
              to force a match, you create Data Redundancy. If Rahul changes his phone number, you now have to update
              it in three different places, causing data mess.

Junction object come in to picture.
-----------------------------------------
Student
Course
Enrollment this is the junction object between student and course.

    One student can have multiple courses, and course can be a multiple students enrolment object will help you.

Note: - {Salesforce Recommends to go with masterdetails not lookup Because it uses Master-Detail relationships,
          if you delete Rahul from the school, Salesforce automatically triggers a Cascade Deletion and wipes
          out his 3 enrollment records instantly. This keeps your database perfectly clean with zero orphaned data.}


